  "prompt": "What are the best Indian gaming companies that builds small open world, first-person shooter, 3d games for Ios that you can hire so they can make games for you?",
  "response": "There are several Indian gaming companies known for their expertise in developing mobile games, including small open-world, first-person shooter, and 3D games for iOS. Here are some of the notable ones:\n\n1. **Nodding Heads Games**: Known for their detailed storytelling and immersive gameplay, Nodding Heads Games specializes in quality gaming experiences. They are known for their strategy and action games and have a good reputation in the industry.\n\n2. **Red Dot Games**: This company focuses on high-quality mobile games and has experience with 3D graphics. They can be a good option if you're looking for custom game development with a focus on mobile platforms.\n\n3. **Nazara Technologies**: A prominent player in the Indian gaming sector, Nazara owns several game studios and has the capability to develop different genres, including action and FPS games.\n\n4. **Octro, Inc.**: While they are primarily known for casual games, Octro has a strong development team that can handle various types of game projects, including those with more complex mechanics.\n\n5. **Zynga India**: This is the Indian branch of the well-known international gaming company Zynga. They have a track record of producing successful mobile games and can potentially take on new FPS projects.\n\n6. **Games2win**: They focus on mobile games and have a solid background in developing diverse game genres. Their experience with innovative gameplay mechanics can be beneficial.\n\n7. **Rolocule Games**: They specialize in developing high-quality, graphically rich games for mobile devices. Their expertise in 3D games could be particularly useful for your project.\n\n8. **Gameloft India**: Part of the global Gameloft company, their Indian studio has a range of talent and experience in developing various types of mobile games, including shooters and open-world titles.\n\nWhen considering a partnership, it\u2019s essential to assess their portfolio, understand their previous work, and evaluate their expertise in the specific genre you are interested in. Always ensure to engage with the companies directly to discuss your project scope, timelines, and budget.",
